AllowPlayers is a simple plugin for bukkit which allows players access
to a server that runs in online mode when minecraft.net is down.

Dependencies:
  - AdminCmd:   http://dev.bukkit.org/server-mods/admincmd/
   OR
  - Essentials: http://dev.bukkit.org/server-mods/essentials/

Commands:
  - allowplayers - Manage AllowPlayers
    - Aliases: ap
    - Usage: /<command> [check|enable|disable|reload]
             /<command> set <player> <IP>

  - onlinemode - Sets the server's online mode state
    - Aliases: om
    - Usage: /<command> [status|enable|disable]

Permissions:
  - allowplayers.command.ap         - Access the allowplayers command
  - allowplayers.command.check      - Force a Minecraft.net check
  - allowplayers.command.reload     - Reload the configuration
  - allowplayers.command.onlinemode - Set the server's online mode
  - allowplayers.command.set        - Set a player's IP
  - allowplayers.command.toggle     - Toggle AllowPlayers on or off
  - allowplayers.message.notify     - View Minecraft.net status messages
